other_tests.findings: A 9 x 7 mm appendicolith is seen with the appendix dilated up to 12 mm and surrounding inflammatory fat stranding. A smaller appendicolith measuring 3 mm is seen near the tip. Mild bilateral dependent atelectasis in the lung bases. No free air or fluid collection is noted. Presence of colonic diverticulosis and several likely reactive lymph nodes in the right lower quadrant.
